If the problem of the Czech researchers accused in India of illegal cockroach harvesting is not resolved, Czech Foreign Minister Karel Schwarzenberg said there would be some cooling of Czech-Indian relations.
The minister said today in New York, after meeting with his Indian counterpart Pranab Mukherjee.
"If the problem was not resolved, then yes, some cooling would occur," he noted after the meeting, which was held following a Czech initiative.
Mukherjee said after the talks that it was difficult for the executive branch to intervene in judicial matters.
He mentioned, however, that in the case of Petr <0xC5><0xA0>vácha, who was discharged from the accusation and fined, the central government could negotiate with the local government, the Darjeling government, the case being placed under the jurisdiction of the latter.
"His problem could be solved," said the minister.
